Mirror World
------------


The Mirror World consists of projectors,mirrors and blocks.
Mirrors reflect light, projectors emit light and blocks absord light.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

To run the code, first compile it using the following command:

g++ Assignment1.cpp -lglut -lGL -lGLU

Once the file is compiled,run it using the command:

./a.out

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Execution

Mirror World consists of 4 modes:
Static mode : 
Random Walk Mode : Use the z key enter and exit the random walk mode.
Light Transport Mode : Use the t key enter and exit this mode.
Gaze at Cursor Mode : Use the g key enter and exit this mode.

Following are the controls:

Esc key or 'q' key : Exit the mirror World. It saves the world configuration in backup file.
'p' key : Insert a projector.
'm' key : Insert a mirror.
'b' key : Insert a block.
'c' key : Select an object. Repeatedly clicking c changes the selection through all the objects.
'r' key : Rotate an object in clockwise direction.
'l' key : Rotate an object in anti-clockwise direction.
'f' key : Make any subsequent translation/rotation faster.
's' key : Make any subsequent translation/rotation slower.
'z' key : Enter and exit the random walk mode.
't' key : Enter and exit the light transport mode.
'g' key : Enter and exit the gaze at cursor mode.
Arrow keys : Translate the objects in different directions.

